headline: Bessent Calls for Simplified Fed as He Ends Candidate Interviews
summary: “One of the things in terms of the criteria that I’ve been looking for” has been the interplay of the Fed’s various instruments, Bessent said on CNBC Tuesday.  “I realize the Fed has become this very complicated operation.”  Bessent said his final second-round interview with the five candidates to succeed Chair Jerome Powell will be today, and reiterated that President Donald Trump may make his announcement on the nomination before Dec. 25.

headline: Bitcoin Retreats as Traders See Signs Worst of Selloff Is Over
summary: Bitcoin recovered slightly and was trading at around $87,500 at 6:39 a.m. in New York.  Bitcoin remains on track for its worst month since 2022, and exchange-traded funds investing in the token look likely to record their heaviest monthly outflows since launching.  In the Bitcoin options market, the cost of purchasing downside protection has fallen sharply, with the premium for one-week puts over calls sliding to around 4.5% from a 2025 high of 11% reached on Friday, according to Caroline Mauron, co-founder of Orbit Markets.
